{"id":414100,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bill_Gold","text":"William \"Bill\" Gold (January 3, 1921 \u2013 May 20, 2018) was an American graphic designer best known for thousands of movie poster designs.\nHis first movie poster was for \"Yankee Doodle Dandy\" (1941), and his most recent and final work was for \"J. Edgar\" (2011).\nDuring his 70-year career he has worked with some of Hollywood's greatest filmmakers, including Laurence Olivier, Clint Eastwood, Alfred Hitchcock, Stanley Kubrick, Elia Kazan, Fran\u00E7ois Truffaut, Ron Howard, Sidney Lumet, Ridley Scott, and Ray Harryhausen.\nAmong his most famous movie posters are those for \"Casablanca\", \"A Streetcar Named Desire\", \"The Exorcist\", \"A Clockwork Orange\", \"Escape from Alcatraz\", and \"Alien\".\nGold was born on January 3, 1921 in New York City, New York. He died at his home in Old Greenwich, Connecticut on May 20, 2018 of complications from Alzheimer's disease at the age of 97.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Americans","surface_form":"American","offset":60},{"uri":"Graphic_designer","surface_form":"graphic designer","offset":69},{"uri":"Movie_poster","surface_form":"movie poster","offset":114},{"uri":"Movie_poster","surface_form":"movie poster","offset":146},{"uri":"Yankee_Doodle_Dandy","surface_form":"Yankee Doodle Dandy","offset":168},{"uri":"J._Edgar","surface_form":"J. Edgar","offset":241},{"uri":"Laurence_Olivier","surface_form":"Laurence Olivier","offset":355},{"uri":"Clint_Eastwood","surface_form":"Clint Eastwood","offset":373},{"uri":"Alfred_Hitchcock","surface_form":"Alfred Hitchcock","offset":389},{"uri":"Stanley_Kubrick","surface_form":"Stanley Kubrick","offset":407},{"uri":"Elia_Kazan","surface_form":"Elia Kazan","offset":424},{"uri":"Fran%C3%A7ois_Truffaut","surface_form":"Fran\u00E7ois Truffaut","offset":436},{"uri":"Ron_Howard","surface_form":"Ron Howard","offset":455},{"uri":"Sidney_Lumet","surface_form":"Sidney Lumet","offset":467},{"uri":"Ridl